The paper deals with scheduling jobs on machines, which is a classic problem in combinatorial optimization. This problem can be categorized under several sub-fields of computer science, such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), game theory (cs.GT), and information theory (cs.IT). However, since the paper focuses on the approximation algorithm for the problem, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.DS or cs.DM. The other categories are also possible, but less likely.
